picked:
Who played the girl elf in "The Hobbit" trilogy as portrayed by J. R. R. Tolkien?
Tauriel is a fictional character from J. R. R. Tolkien's Middle-earth legendarium. She appears in the 2012–2014 film adaptations of The Hobbit as an original character created by the film's screenwriters. Tauriel is portrayed by Evangeline Lilly in all three films.
Tauriel is a Silvan Elf of Mirkwood and Captain of Thranduil's Guard. In The Hobbit films, Tauriel forms a friendship with Thorin Oakenshield's company of Dwarves and becomes romantically involved with one of them, Kili. In The Battle of the Five Armies, she aids Thorin in his battle against the armies of Men, Dwarves, and Elves who have come to claim a share of the treasure Thorin's company acquired from the Lonely Mountain. Although Tauriel is not mentioned in The Lord of the Rings or The Hobbit, Lilly's portrayal of the character was well-received, with critics praising her performance and character development.
Other notable actresses who were considered for the role of Tauriel included Rooney Mara, Jessica Brown Findlay, and Kate Beckinsale.
